textAnnotations.description:
SAUGUS SCHOOL BELL
The bell in the tower of
this station was fabricated by the
C.S. Bell Company of Hillsboro,
Ohio. It weighs approximately
400 pounds and measures 30
inches in diameter at the base.
The bell originally hung in the belfry of Saugus
Elementary School, which opened in 1908 on
farmland between present-day Magic Mountain
Parkway and Bouquet Junction. The school was
closed in the 1977-78 school year, and the bell was
transferred to the Santa Clarita Valley Historical
Society. It was then placed on permanent loan with
the City of Santa Clarita at the JAN HEIDT
METROLINK STATION.
Sala Crla Vy
HISTORICAL
Cociely
Dedicated on March 18, 2000
